<div class="mlp-docs-card">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-list"></i> Data We Collect</div>
<ul class="mlp-docs-list">
<li><strong>IP Addresses:</strong> Collected temporarily per request to enforce AI cooldown limits and prevent abuse</li>
<li><strong>Shared Code Snippets:</strong> When you use the Share feature, your HTML/CSS/JS code is stored in our database linked to a unique share ID</li>
<li><strong>AI Prompts:</strong> Prompts sent to our AI assistant are logged temporarily for caching and abuse prevention</li>
<li><strong>Browser LocalStorage:</strong> Backups are stored locally on your own device — we do not have access to this data</li>
<li><strong>WordPress Session Data:</strong> Standard WordPress session and nonce tokens for security</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-card mlp-docs-card-info">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-user-secret"></i> What We Do NOT Collect</div>
<ul class="mlp-docs-list">
<li>We do not require account registration to use the editor</li>
<li>We do not collect your name, email, or personal identifying information unless you register on the WordPress site</li>
<li>We do not sell your data to advertisers or third parties</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-section" data-section="pp-2">
<div class="mlp-docs-section-heading"><i class="fas fa-cog"></i> How We Use Data</div>
<p class="mlp-docs-lead">All data collected is used exclusively for operating ptero.eu.cc and ensuring a safe, fair experience for all users.</p>
<div class="mlp-docs-card">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-tasks"></i> Data Usage Purposes</div>
<ul class="mlp-docs-list">
<li><strong>IP Data:</strong> Used to enforce the AI request cooldown (60 seconds per IP) and share rate limits (30 requests/minute). In v5.9.0, rate-limit counters are stored in a high-speed in-memory cache (Redis/APCu) and never written to a permanent log &mdash; they expire naturally after the window closes</li>
<li><strong>Shared Snippets:</strong> Stored to provide shareable preview links. Expired shares are deleted automatically by the hourly cleanup job.</li>
<li><strong>AI Prompts:</strong> Cached for up to <strong>1 hour</strong> (not 24 hours as in previous versions) at two layers: in-memory cache first, then database. This reduces redundant API calls and returns repeat responses in milliseconds</li>
<li><strong>Global AI Counter:</strong> An anonymous daily counter tracks total AI requests across all users against the 10,000/day cap. This counter contains no personal data &mdash; it is a single number incremented atomically</li>
<li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Aggregate, anonymized usage statistics may be collected to improve the platform</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-section" data-section="pp-3">
<div class="mlp-docs-section-heading"><i class="fas fa-server"></i> Data Storage &amp; Security</div>
<p class="mlp-docs-lead">We take reasonable technical measures to secure the data stored on our servers. v5.9.0 significantly reduces the amount of personal data touching the database.</p>
<div class="mlp-docs-card">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-lock"></i> Security Measures</div>
<ul class="mlp-docs-list">
<li>All API requests are validated with WordPress nonces to prevent CSRF attacks</li>
<li>Share URL parameters are encrypted with <strong>AES-256-GCM</strong> to prevent tampering in transit</li>
<li>IP addresses used for rate limiting are now stored in an <strong>in-memory cache only</strong> &mdash; they are never written to a permanent database record for rate-limit purposes</li>
<li>AI cache and queue tables are automatically pruned in hourly batches &mdash; data is never kept longer than necessary</li>
<li>Shared code links use opaque random identifiers &mdash; not linked to personal identity</li>
<li>Circuit breaker state (AI service health) is stored in the object cache and synced to the database only on state transitions &mdash; not on every request</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-card mlp-docs-card-warning">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> Important Notice</div>
<p>Do not share sensitive or confidential code using the Share feature.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-section" data-section="pp-5">
<div class="mlp-docs-section-heading"><i class="fas fa-cookie-bite"></i> Cookies</div>
<p class="mlp-docs-lead">ptero.eu.cc uses minimal cookies, limited to what WordPress requires for standard functionality.</p>
<div class="mlp-docs-card">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> Cookie Usage</div>
<ul class="mlp-docs-list">
<li><strong>WordPress Session Cookies:</strong> Used for logged-in WordPress users only</li>
<li><strong>Security Nonces:</strong> Short-lived tokens embedded in page markup, not cookie-based</li>
<li>We do not use tracking cookies, advertising cookies, or third-party analytics cookies</li>
<li>LocalStorage is used for your code backups — this is stored only on your device</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-section" data-section="pp-6">
<div class="mlp-docs-section-heading"><i class="fas fa-user-check"></i> Your Rights</div>
<p class="mlp-docs-lead">You have rights regarding any personal data we may hold about you.</p>
<div class="mlp-docs-card">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-hand-paper"></i> Your Rights Include</div>
<ul class="mlp-docs-list">
<li><strong>Right to Know:</strong> You may request a summary of what data we hold related to your IP or account</li>
<li><strong>Right to Deletion:</strong> You may request deletion of your shared code snippets by contacting us with the share URL</li>
<li><strong>Right to Withdraw:</strong> You may stop using ptero.eu.cc at any time — no data is tied to a mandatory account</li>
<li><strong>Local Data:</strong> Your browser backup data is fully under your control — you can clear it via your browser's developer tools</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-section" data-section="pp-7">
<div class="mlp-docs-section-heading"><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Data Retention</div>
<p class="mlp-docs-lead">We retain data only for as long as necessary for platform operation. v5.9.0 reduces retention windows and moves short-lived data out of the database entirely.</p>
<div class="mlp-docs-card">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-table"></i> Retention Schedule (v5.9.0)</div>
<ul class="mlp-docs-list">
<li><strong>Rate-Limit Counters (IP):</strong> Stored in in-memory cache only &mdash; never persisted to disk. Expire automatically after 60&ndash;65 seconds</li>
<li><strong>Shared Code:</strong> Retained until the share expiration date you set (1&ndash;10 minutes), then deleted in the next hourly cleanup batch. Maximum 100,000 records kept</li>
<li><strong>Anomaly Log:</strong> Last 500 security events kept in the database (IPs are partially redacted before storage). Oldest entries are dropped when the limit is reached</li>
<li><strong>WordPress User Data:</strong> Retained per WordPress standard for registered accounts</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-section" data-section="pp-infra">
<div class="mlp-docs-section-heading"><i class="fas fa-bolt" style="color:#f0c040;"></i> Performance Infrastructure &amp; Your Data (v5.9.0)</div>
<p class="mlp-docs-lead">The v5.9.0 infrastructure upgrade changes how and where your data is processed. This section explains the implications for your privacy.</p>
<div class="mlp-docs-card" style="border-color:rgba(240,192,64,0.4);background:rgba(240,192,64,0.05);">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-memory"></i> In-Memory Object Cache (Redis / APCu)</div>
<p>To handle high traffic, the platform now uses an <strong>in-memory object cache</strong> (Redis or APCu, depending on server configuration). The following data may live in this cache:</p>
<ul class="mlp-docs-list" style="margin-top:8px;">
<li><strong>Rate-limit hit counts</strong> keyed to a hashed version of your IP address &mdash; the hash is one-way and cannot be reversed to recover your original IP</li>
</ul>
<p style="margin-top:8px;">This in-memory data is <strong>volatile</strong>: it is lost on server restart and is never written to disk by this plugin.</p>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-card">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> What This Means for Privacy</div>
<ul class="mlp-docs-list">
<li>Your IP address is now processed in-memory (not in the database) for rate-limiting purposes &mdash; this is a privacy improvement over previous versions</li>
<li>If your server uses Redis, a system administrator with Redis access could theoretically read hashed rate-limit keys, but not your original IP</li>
<li>No new categories of personal data are collected &mdash; only the <em>location</em> of data processing has changed (memory vs. database)</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-card mlp-docs-card-info">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> Object Cache Availability</div>
<p>The in-memory object cache is only active if the server has Redis or APCu installed with a WordPress object-cache drop-in. If not available, the plugin falls back to WordPress transients (database-backed). The same data is processed in both cases &mdash; only the storage medium differs. This section applies equally to both paths.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-section" data-section="pp-8">
<div class="mlp-docs-section-heading"><i class="fas fa-envelope"></i> Contact</div>
<p class="mlp-docs-lead">If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or wish to exercise your data rights, you may contact us.</p>
<div class="mlp-docs-card mlp-docs-card-info">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-at"></i> Contact Information</div>
<p>You can reach the ptero.eu.cc team via the contact page on the website. For data deletion requests, include the specific share URL or your account username. We aim to respond to all privacy-related requests within 7 business days.</p>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-card">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-calendar"></i> Policy Updates</div>
<p>This Privacy Policy was last updated in <strong>March 2026 (v5.9.0)</strong>. We reserve the right to update this policy at any time. Continued use of ptero.eu.cc following an update constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><!-- /mlp-docs-main -->
</div><!-- /mlp-docs-body -->
</div>
</div>
